body: When I was a kid we used to call Spider-Man “失败的 man” (pinyin: shi1-bai4-de man), which basically translates to “man who is a failure/who fails.” Did anybody else do this or was it just me and my friends?

reblog.comment: When I was a kid we used to call Spider-Man “失败的 man” (pinyin: shi1-bai4-de man), which basically translates to “man who is a failure/who fails.” Did anybody else do this or was it just me and my friends?

summary: Peter Parker while listening to Sympathy for the Devil: I’ve been called the Devil all my life. So empowering. Such...
body:
Peter Parker while listening to Sympathy for the Devil: I’ve been called the Devil all my life. So empowering. Such movement.


Tony Stark scoffing: No one has ever called you a Devil a day in your life. They call you an excited puppy that climbs walls.


Stephen Strange: Honey, just let him believe.
